The article is a speech given by the First Lady, Michelle Obama, in Alexandria, Virginia. She thanks Major General Angle for his service and acknowledges the work of special forces, highlighting the challenges they face and the support they need. She mentions her White House initiative, Joining Forces, which aims to support military and veteran families, caregivers, and survivors. The initiative focuses on creating career and entrepreneurship opportunities for spouses, providing quality child care, supporting military kids' education, and improving resources for military family health and wellbeing. Obama emphasizes the importance of not asking special forces to choose between their love of country and their love of family, stating that it is a national security imperative. She expresses gratitude for their service and sacrifice and assures them that she and the President stand with them.